::DarkMouse::

She could feel a hand pat her on the shoulder and head.  It felt warm 
and comforting.  She felt cold, but who ever was petting her, she 
would thank later on.  It made her feel good in knowing that this 
wasn't all a dream, but that she really was alive.  She sniffed the 
air and recognized the scent, BlackAracnia.  She would thank her 
later when she was able to.  She tried to open her eyes and move her 
body, but it wouldn't respond to her.  She heard her spark slow it's 
thundering down to a steady normal pace.
